# Plan backlog development

When the user asks to **execute the plan**, **work the backlog**, or **run plan agents**, orchestrate from `plan/manifest.json`.

## Bootstrap

1. Load `.cursor/skills/plan-orchestrator/SKILL.md`
2. Read `plan/manifest.json` and `plan/README.md`
3. Pick next eligible story (phase → priority → dependsOn)

## Per-story loop

1. **Master** — assign story to agent from manifest; set `IN-PROGRESS`
2. **Specialist** — load agent skill; implement child tasks; mark tasks `DONE`
3. **QA** — load `performance-qa` skill; validate; report PASS/FAIL
4. **Close** — on PASS, set story `DONE` in manifest + USER-STORIES.md

## Agent skills map

| Agent | Skill(s) | Stories |
|-------|----------|---------|
| NextJS Developer | nextjs-performance, database-migrations | US-F-*, US-B-*, US-D-* |
| React Native Developer | mobile-performance | US-M-* |
| QA Specialist | performance-qa | All validation; owns US-B-016 |

## Continue until

- All stories DONE, or blocked, or user stops
- Report progress every story: "Done [N]/30, next [US-*]"

Do not ask permission between stories unless blocked.

Reference: `plan/agents/master.md`, `AGENTS.md`.
